124
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:14,006
I'd like us to imagine a
world without tuberculosis.

125
00:06:14,006 --> 00:06:19,879
This is the Granville mummy,
estimated to be found in 600 BC.

126
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:22,014
At the time when they
unearthed this mummy,

127
00:06:22,014 --> 00:06:24,150
they thought that the cause
of death for this mummy

128
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:25,852
was ovarian cancer.

129
00:06:25,852 --> 00:06:29,589
However, in the early 2000s,
researchers found that this

130
00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:32,458
mummy had had tuberculosis.

131
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:35,027
Fast forward to
the 19th century,

132
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:39,031
where it's estimated that one in
seven individuals was dying from

133
00:06:39,031 --> 00:06:40,166
tuberculosis.

134
00:06:40,166 --> 00:06:44,137
This is an ad from the Christmas
Seals asking you to donate money

135
00:06:44,137 --> 00:06:45,972
to stamp out tuberculosis.

136
00:06:45,972 --> 00:06:48,708
But unfortunately, I'm here to
report that the Christmas Seals

137
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:52,912
were unsuccessful in this
campaign because today alone,

138
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:56,349
4,000 people will die from TB.

139
00:06:56,349 --> 00:06:59,118
OK, so what would
be transformative?

140
00:06:59,118 --> 00:07:02,522
What would be transformative
for TB is a protective vaccine.

141
00:07:02,522 --> 00:07:04,991
And this is something
that we do not yet have.

142
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:07,760
We have one vaccine for TB.

143
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:12,365
It is over 100 years old, and it
doesn't meet the product profile

144
00:07:12,365 --> 00:07:14,400
needed to end this pandemic.

145
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:18,704
However, if we did, it
would change history.

146
00:07:18,704 --> 00:07:21,707
So looking at this graph, this
is TB incidence per million

147
00:07:21,707 --> 00:07:25,445
on the y-axis and
time on the x-axis.

148
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:28,748
If we do nothing and we
just keep standard of care,

149
00:07:28,748 --> 00:07:30,316
that's the red line.

150
00:07:30,316 --> 00:07:34,687
If we had a 60% protective
vaccine and a mass vaccination

151
00:07:34,687 --> 00:07:37,523
campaign, look at
what could happen.

152
00:07:37,523 --> 00:07:41,093
All right, so the question
becomes, how do we get there?

153
00:07:41,093 --> 00:07:44,230
How do we make a
protective TB vaccine?

154
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:45,598
All right, so
that's the question

155
00:07:45,598 --> 00:07:47,600
that my lab decided to tackle.

156
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,703
So why aren't we there yet?

157
00:07:50,703 --> 00:07:52,071
We heard about measurement.

158
00:07:52,071 --> 00:07:54,407
I would like to submit to you
that this is a measurement

159
00:07:54,407 --> 00:07:55,942
problem.

160
00:07:55,942 --> 00:07:57,543
So the question
becomes, how do you

161
00:07:57,543 --> 00:07:59,545
design a vaccine
in the first place?

162
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:01,948
We might all be experts
about designing vaccines

163
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:04,617
for viral pathogens,
but tuberculosis

164
00:08:04,617 --> 00:08:06,352
is caused by a bacterium.

165
00:08:06,352 --> 00:08:09,322
So when I think about this
problem as an engineer,

166
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,858
I think about the
following question, what

167
00:08:11,858 --> 00:08:15,695
proteins from the bacterium
does the immune system see?

168
00:08:15,695 --> 00:08:18,397
All right, this is an
especially hard problem

169
00:08:18,397 --> 00:08:20,833
in the context of
infection with bacteria

170
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,703
because viruses have
tens of proteins.

171
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:26,572
TB has 4,000.

172
00:08:26,572 --> 00:08:30,276
So it's not that simple just
to say which protein do I pick.

173
00:08:30,276 --> 00:08:32,178
It's actually a
really hard problem.

174
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:35,281
And to make that problem even
just a smidge more difficult,

175
00:08:35,281 --> 00:08:37,083
we have to do this
in a biosafety level

176
00:08:37,083 --> 00:08:40,820
three environment, which
means that everything just

177
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:44,624
goes much slower, much more
complicated, and much more

178
00:08:44,624 --> 00:08:47,493
arduous, because this isn't some
place where you can just say,

179
00:08:47,493 --> 00:08:49,962
I want to try something
new and do it tomorrow.

180
00:08:49,962 --> 00:08:51,931
This takes a lot of
effort and energy.

181
00:08:51,931 --> 00:08:55,167
So despite those roadblocks, I'm
really excited to share with you

182
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:57,870
that we've made significant
inroads to this problem.

183
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,839
OK, so how do we do this?

184
00:08:59,839 --> 00:09:02,375
So work led by an
incredibly talented graduate

185
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,610
student in collaboration
with Forrest White.

186
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:07,513
We set out to address
the measurement problem,

187
00:09:07,513 --> 00:09:10,016
asking specifically
in human cells

188
00:09:10,016 --> 00:09:12,552
across diverse human
genotypes, if we

189
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:15,788
infect with TB, what
proteins from the bacterium

190
00:09:15,788 --> 00:09:17,690
are seen by the immune system?

191
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,892
So I'm going to call
this problem solved.

192
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:20,626
We can do it.

193
00:09:20,626 --> 00:09:22,662
We can do it within days now.

194
00:09:22,662 --> 00:09:24,997
OK, So now the next
question becomes,

195
00:09:24,997 --> 00:09:26,432
if you can make
these measurements

196
00:09:26,432 --> 00:09:30,136
and ask what the immune
system sees with bacteria,

197
00:09:30,136 --> 00:09:33,606
can we ask what does
the immune system see

198
00:09:33,606 --> 00:09:37,109
when you give a vaccine,
including those proteins

199
00:09:37,109 --> 00:09:38,477
from the bacterium?

200
00:09:38,477 --> 00:09:40,279
And that's what we've
been able to do now.

201
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:43,282
So now we can design
vaccines as mRNAs

202
00:09:43,282 --> 00:09:46,452
and within weeks get an answer
about a particular design

203
00:09:46,452 --> 00:09:47,286
that we've made.

204
00:09:47,286 --> 00:09:49,355
And to give you an example
of what we've done just

205
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:52,658
in the last few years, is we've
made all these different vaccine

206
00:09:52,658 --> 00:09:55,428
prototypes, and I don't have
the time to go through all

207
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:59,165
the details, but what we can
do now with these measurement

208
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:02,134
technologies and say, what if
we change just one parameter

209
00:10:02,134 --> 00:10:03,769
about this mRNA vaccine?

210
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:05,571
How does it change
immune output?

211
00:10:05,571 --> 00:10:08,341
So that's what you're looking at
